-- ECB's Noyer Says French Pension Reform Needed, Will Get Harder If Dropped
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2010-10-14T05:59:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/ecb-s-noyer-says-french-pension-reform-needed-will-get-harder-if-dropped.html
European Central Bank Governing
Council member Christian Noyer said French pension reform is
“entirely necessary,” and there will be “harder choices” in
the future if pensions are not reformed. Noyer spoke in an
interview on France’s RTL radio today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg at 
 rruitenberg@bloomberg.net  